TWO siblings, aged 11 and 14, have been arrested for stealing a collection of firearms and ammunition from a gun shop. After unsuccessfully attempting to cut power to the business and prying open a rear door, the brothers, from Florida, USA, entered Guns 4 Less in Cape Coral around 3am on Wednesday. As they smashed display cases, cops received an alarm alerting them to the break-in. READ:Â DUMB Tsotsi bust hiding in the roof! The New York Post reports that officers spotted them running from the scene armed with multiple handguns, ammunition, magazines and long guns. They eventually dropped the guns on the street due to their weight. But they were eventually found. They now face 22 counts of grand theft of a firearm and one of armed burglary.